title: For Sale:  Blackhole Weaponry AR-10/308
postcontent: Up for sale is a custom built Ar-10/308 hyrbid using a Matrix Aerospace upper and lower matching receiver set. The Matrix receiver set allows the build to use either Armalite or DPMS components. The build centered around a custom order 20" Blackhole Weaponry Stainless 1/11 twist bull barrel, with 5/8-24 threads and rifle length gas. The handguard is a Midwest Industries 15" SSK keymod (Armalite style barrel nut), with a Troy industries low profile gas block, and actual JP Bennie Cooley muzzle brake. The barrel nut is properly torqued on at 60 ft/lbs, and the bolt carrier group is a DPMS Nickel Boron coated unit sans forward assist serrations. The stock is a LUTH-AR Skullaton with a proper DPMS LR-308 rifle spring and buffer installed. It was built with an Armalite lower parts kit, and also rocks a Rock River Varmint 3.5lb 2 stage trigger, and Ergo rubberized Palm swell grip. Lastly it also has a BCM Gunfighter charging handle with the large latch. The rifle was built a couple years ago and has maybe 80 rounds through it and shoots very smooth with minimal recoil for a 308, and otherwise has just been sitting around seeing minimal use due to the high cost of 308. Only reason it's up for sale is because I already have several other 308's and I'd prefer something cheaper to shoot. This gun is a purpose built bench/target/sniper type rifle, and is fairly heavy due to the bull barrel and large frame...but is easily sub MOA accurate. With handloads or good factory ammo, it should be 1/2 MOA capable or less actually, as I've personally shot around .6 MOA with factory match ammo. The gun takes all styles of LR-308/Magpul/DPMS mags, and I can include an Armalite small parts kit you can use to swap out the mag catch to make it Armalite magazine compatible as well. I will say upfront that the bolt catch on the rifle doesn't work too well with LR-308 style mags, and doesn't hold the bolt back reliably when manually activated, but an empty mag does for the most part. It's likely due to the fact the bolt catch is an Armalite AR-10A catch, but swapping it out for a DPMS catch (A rougly $8 part) will likely do the trick. It never bothered me that much so I haven't swapped it yet. Other than that, the gun has some light handling marks and a few tiny scratches in a few places, but other than that is in excellent shape. If you wish to see more pics just email me and I can provide any angle or whatever requested. I will include everything seen in the pics (except the mag) with the gun, including the scope and mount, and bipod and picatinny keymod rail mount. The Scope isn't great...it's a Tasco 6x-24x 42mm, but it'll get the job done.I would consider shipping this rifle anywhere in state for $45 shipping.I also am willing to accept discreet paypal payment + 3.5% of the sales price.Please, no trades.
